## Content Attribution

The quotes in this project are sourced from the following traditions:

### Kabbalistic Sources
- **Baal HaSulam (Rabbi Yehuda Ashlag, 1884-1954)**: Commentaries on the Zohar
  and original writings are in the public domain. Modern translations and
  compilations may be subject to separate copyright.

- **RABASH (Rabbi Baruch Shalom Ashlag, 1907-1991)**: Writings are in the
  public domain.

- **Arizal (Rabbi Isaac Luria, 1534-1572)**: Classical Kabbalistic texts in
  the public domain.

### Chassidic Sources
- **Baal Shem Tov (Rabbi Israel ben Eliezer, 1698-1760)**: Oral teachings
  recorded by students, in the public domain.

- **Kotzker Rebbe (Rabbi Menachem Mendel of Kotzk, 1787-1859)**: Oral
  teachings in the public domain.

- **Rabbi Simcha Bunim of Peshischa (1765-1827)**: Oral teachings in the
  public domain.

### Source References
Quotes include references to:
- [Kabbalah.info](https://www.kabbalah.info/) - Bnei Baruch's educational platform
- [Sefaria.org](https://www.sefaria.org/) - Open source Jewish text library

We encourage users to explore these original sources for deeper study.

